---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility | Summit Fitness & CrossFit"
  description="Summit Fitness & CrossFit is committed to digital accessibility. Learn about our WCAG AA compliance and how to request accommodations."
>
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-zinc-950" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="w-12 h-1 bg-orange-600" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <h1 id="hero-heading" class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight">
          Accessibility
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-12">Our commitment to an inclusive experience for everyone.</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-10 text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">

        <section aria-labelledby="commitment-heading">
          <h2 id="commitment-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
          <p>Summit Fitness & CrossFit is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We continually improve the user experience for everyone and apply relevant accessibility standards to ensure we meet that commitment.</p>
          <div class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-orange-600/10 border border-orange-600/30 rounded-lg px-6 py-4">
            <span class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-orange-500">10/10</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-white">WAVE Accessibility Score</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Verified across all pages</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="standards-heading">
          <h2 id="standards-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Conformance Standards</h2>
          <p>This website conforms to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible to people with disabilities.</p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="features-heading">
          <h2 id="features-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Accessibility Features</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mt-4 text-zinc-400">
            <li>Skip to main content link for keyboard navigation</li>
            <li>Proper heading hierarchy throughout all pages</li>
            <li>All images include descriptive alternative text</li>
            <li>All form inputs have associated labels</li>
            <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios on all text</li>
            <li>All interactive elements are keyboard accessible</li>
            <li>ARIA landmarks and labels on all page regions</li>
            <li>Reduced motion support for users who prefer it</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="physical-heading">
          <h2 id="physical-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Physical Accessibility</h2>
          <p>Our facility is designed to be accessible to all members:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mt-4 text-zinc-400">
            <li>Accessible entrance and parking</li>
            <li>Accessible restrooms and locker rooms</li>
            <li>All workout areas are accessible</li>
            <li>Coaches trained to work with adaptive athletes</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="feedback-heading">
          <h2 id="feedback-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Feedback & Contact</h2>
          <p>We welcome feedback on the accessibility of our website and facility. If you experience any barriers or need accommodations, please contact us:</p>
          <address class="not-italic mt-4 text-zinc-400">
            Summit Fitness & CrossFit<br />
            123 Fitness Way, Littleton, NH 03561<br />
            <a href="tel:+15551234567" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">(555) 123-4567</a><br />
            <a href="mailto:info@summitfitness.com" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">info@summitfitness.com</a>
          </address>
          <p class="mt-4">We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days.</p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>